				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Let me stress that last bit: <em>What is special about M as a piece of evidence</em>? What distinguishes the significance of &#8220;GTR predicts M&#8221; from the significance of &#8220;GTR predicts the 10^100th rock will fall down&#8221;? It&#8217;s not in the math.</p>
<p id="comment-like-589" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://carcinisation.com/2014/09/26/the-old-evidence-problem/?like_comment=589&#038;_wpnonce=9eaf40a747" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="71183487"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-589" class="comment-like-feedback">Liked by <a href="#" class="view-likers" data-like-count="1">1 person</a></span></p>
